The paper discusses the use of BCH codes in communication, data storage, and information security, which are all related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the study of cyclic codes over finite fields, which falls under the category of discrete structures (cs.DS). The investigation of coset leaders modulo n and the determination of dimensions of BCH codes involve algebraic techniques, which could be relevant to cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of new techniques, which could be related to signal processing (cs.SI) or networking (cs.NI).
